4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING TRAPPERS TO POST NOTICE SIGNS WITHIN
5 CERTAIN DISTANCES OF TRAILHEADS AND TRAILS ON PUBLIC LANDS ADMINISTERED BY THE
6 DEPARTMENT OF FISH, WILDLIFE, AND PARKS; PROVIDING SIGNAGE REQUIREMENTS; AND
7 PROVIDING DEFINITIONS.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Notice signs for traps and snares on public lands -- definitions. (1) A
12 trapper shall post a notice sign at a trailhead on public lands administered by the department where traps or
13 snares are located within 1,000 feet of the trailhead or within 100 feet of any point of a public trail marked by a
14 trailhead. If no trailhead exists, the sign must be posted at the point where a trapper accessed a public trail if
15 the traps or snares are located within 100 feet of the trail at any point.
16 (2) The department shall provide a downloadable, printable notice sign on its website or provide a
17 printed notice sign.
18 (3) The notice sign must:
19 (a) be no smaller than 8 1/2 x 11 inches in size;
20 (b) be able to withstand changing weather conditions;
21 (c) contain the current phone number of the department;
22 (d) contain the following title with letters that are at least 1 inch in height: "Notice: Traps or snares
23 are set in this area."
24 (e) contain the following statement beneath the title: "It is unlawful to destroy, disturb, or remove a
25 trap or snare belonging to another person or to remove wildlife from a trap or snare without permission of the
26 owner of the trap or snare. Exception: From March 1 to October 1 a livestock owner may remove a trap or
27 snare that could endanger livestock. If you disturb a trap or snare, please contact Fish, Wildlife, and Parks."
