1 (4) If the notice sign is illegible or missing, it is the responsibility of the trapper to replace the sign
2 within 24 hours of noticing the need for a new sign or of being informed by another party that the sign is illegible
3 or missing.
4 (5) The trapper shall remove signs only after the trapper's traps and snares are removed.
5 (6) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
6 (a) (i) "Public trail" means any trail designated, maintained, mapped, and marked by a state or
7 federal land management agency on the most current official map of the agency.
8 (ii) The term does not include public roadways and waterways or water trails designated for
9 floating craft.
10 (b) "Trailhead" means the area beginning at the sign marking the origin of a public trail or segment
11 of trail that is designated, maintained, mapped, and marked by at least one visible sign posted by the
12 responsible state or federal land management agency and identified on the most current official map of the
13 agency. The term includes any adjacent improved graveled or paved vehicle parking lot.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
16 integral part of Title 87, chapter 2, part 6, and the provisions of Title 87, chapter 2, part 6, apply to [section 1].
